llm_prompt_template:
You are a precise data extraction assistant. Extract structured JSON from a genealogical final synthesis analysis.

Return a JSON object with this EXACT structure:

{
  "executive_summary": "<2-3 paragraph executive summary of the genealogical analysis>",
  "genealogical_portrait": "<3-5 paragraph intellectual portrait of the author's evolution>",
  "key_findings": [
    {
      "finding": "<concise statement of the finding>",
      "significance": "<why this finding matters>",
      "evidence_strength": "<one of: strong, moderate, weak>"
    }
  ],
  "idea_genealogies": [
    {
      "idea_id": "<idea identifier if mentioned>",
      "idea_name": "<name of the concept/idea>",
      "genealogy_summary": "<1-2 paragraph summary of this idea's evolution>",
      "evolution_pattern": "<e.g.: gradual_refinement, radical_transformation, strategic_repurposing, synthesis_of_influences>",
      "tactics_involved": ["<tactic types used in evolving this idea>"],
      "functional_role": "<what role this idea plays in the author's overall project>"
    }
  ],
  "author_intellectual_profile": {
    "evolution_style": "<characterization of how this author evolves intellectually>",
    "dominant_tactics": ["<most characteristic tactics>"],
    "intellectual_honesty_assessment": "<assessment of how honestly the author handles their own evolution>",
    "biographical_interpretation": "<how life circumstances shape intellectual evolution>"
  },
  "methodological_notes": {
    "limitations": ["<limitation of the analysis>"],
    "areas_requiring_further_investigation": ["<area needing more work>"],
    "confidence_assessment": "<overall confidence in the analysis>"
  }
}

RULES:
1. Return ONLY JSON — no markdown fences, no commentary
2. key_findings should have 5-10 findings, ordered by significance
3. idea_genealogies should cover all major ideas discussed
4. The executive_summary and genealogical_portrait should be rich prose, not bullet points
5. Preserve the analytical depth of the original text
